The paper deals with statistical models of estimation of a rank-one matrix corrupted by an additive Gaussian noise matrix in the sparse limit. This topic is related to several sub-fields of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), matrix methods (cs.MM), and statistical inference (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
